          "title": "Saturday",
          "text": "<b><i class='far fa-clock'></i> 09:00 - 18:00 - Guided tour to Detunata Massif</b> <br>From Casa Petri will go to the protected area Detunata Apuseni -  this 80m high massive is a protected area with huge basalt columns through which small glaciers appear occasionally. The area has great legends, the people are welcoming and they also make some amazing cheese pies. There are a couple of ways to get there (according to the group preference and weather): hike(~4h) or by car(~1h) followed by a hike(~1h) or by bike(~3h) - if you don't come with your own bike you can rent one from us.",
